column2: "Hehehe... this is magnificent, Harriet. To think I was settling for such makeshift contrivances while you were hiding such power."
"Is it because of the catalyst? Or perhaps it is because of your very soul itself?"

"Ah, Harriet!
For you to yield such astounding data...
Indeed, you are the greatest experiment!"
"Brother. What exactly is it you intend to do?"
"I want to try again. My mistakes... I want to undo them."
"And now I actually can! Only now, only I can accomplish it."

"And then... then! With that, I can... I can obtain omniscience.
...Omniscience? What... is omniscience?"
"What... am I doing? Harriet...  What am I doing to my beloved sister, the one person who understood... Ngh... Ugh!!!"
"Heh. Heheh. Hahaha! Look at me, having second thoughts!"
"I shall once again bring back the omniscient one! And then I too shall attain omniscience!"
"Right here, right now! With Ephimera, all that's left is to use the summoning magic to call it forth!"
"I shall obtain omniscience once again, and I shall know all! Hey, Harriet. You understand me, right?"
"You're attempting to transcend the laws of this world. An act that bears no fruit."
"Have you forgotten, Brother? You know exactly what happened here before."
